Description

Public competition at the City of Mendrisio.

Location: 100% indefinite employee or office employee.

Dicastery Institutions and resources Administrative Section Cancelleria Via Municipio 13 6850 Mendrisio 058 688 31 10 stationary@mendrisio.ch Ris. mun. 4910 of 5 May 2026 8 May 2026 Competition for the recruitment of an employee or an office employee 100%, indefinite time, at the Town Hall (AIMsio)

Conditions

The owner of the function is included or included in the Management and Finance Section of the AIM and collaborates with the team in the administrative management of customers, billing and processes connected to the distribution services (electricity, water and gas), ensuring an efficient, accurate and user-oriented service.

Shipments

- advice and assistance to users at the desk, telephone and correspondence, with the management of requests and relative sorting to the competent business areas;
- support for the administrative management of customers and practices connected with the services provided;
- preparation, verification and replacement in the preparation of the advances for the services of competence, transmission of the relative orders and subsequent invoicing;
- support for periodic and extraordinary billing processes of different business services;
- management of calls and administrative recovery of claims relating to consumption bills;
- control, monitoring and reporting of the guarantees required to customers, with updating of the same according to risk and in compliance with internal procedures;
- start of the procedure for laying the measuring systems (contatories) to prepayment and subsequent administrative management;
- support for administrative management of customer changes (new connections, change of ownership, terminations, contractual changes);
- preparation of the correspondence of the Office;
- collection, verification and processing of statistical data and reports to support the activity of the Section;
- collaboration with other business areas for the proper conduct of administrative and operational processes.

In addition:

- other work assignments compatible with its function and its competences may be or are given to it;
- can be called or called to provide service at irregular times, even out of time and on public holidays according to service requirements.

Requirements

Training and experience

- AFC of employees or employees of trade, preferably with professional maturity;
- proven professional experience in the administrative field, preferably in billing, customer management, credit recovery or public services;
- experience in public service companies, utilities or public bodies is preferential.

Professional skills

- ability to perform tasks with precision, reliability, confidentiality and sense of responsibility;
- aptitude for structured work and simultaneous management of more administrative practices;
- good analysis, control and monitoring of administrative and accounting data;
- guidance to service and a strong attitude in managing relationships with users;
- ability to deal with conflict situations with balance, professionalism and constructive approach;
- strong predisposition to group work and interfunctional collaboration.

Language and computer skills

- excellent mastery of the Italian language, written and oral;
- good knowledge of a second national language, preferably of German;
- good mastery of computer tools and the Microsoft Office package;
- knowledge of ERP Abacus and/or CRM is-e is a preferential title.

Other requirements

- home in Switzerland.

What we offer

- annual salary (threeteenth monthly and salary scale updated at 01.01.2026):
- Classes (4)* 5 – 7 ROD (Dependent function)
- Minimum: CHF 62’022.-- annually (*CHF 58’371.--);
- Maximum: CHF 85’327.-- annual;
- in addition to the salary is paid, to the entitled persons, the allowance for children according to LAFam.
- Working week: 40 hours
- Degree of employment: 100%
- Start of activities:
- 1 July 2026 or date to be agreed.
- The first year of service is considered as a test year.

Deadline and Application Mode

Applications must be submitted via the application form by Friday 29 May 2026 at 23:59, accompanied by the following documents:

- presentation letter;
- curriculum vitae with photos;
- copies of certificates of study and work;
- self-certification on good conduct (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio);
- questionnaire on the state of health for the recruitment of personnel to the dependencies of the City of Mendrisio (available from the site of the Municipal Administration of Mendrisio).

Applications submitted in another form will not be considered.

This notice of competition and its application form are also available on the https://www.mendrisio.ch/concourses.

The Human Resources Section remains at the courteous disposal (tel. +41 58 688 33 10) of those who do not have a device (PC, tablet, smartphone, scanner, etc.) to provide them with the necessary tools to send their application through the prescribed application form.

In addition to the documents to be attached to the application, at a later time may be required to present the extract of the court for private individuals and the extract of the execution register (validity 6 months).

The City Hall reserves the right to change the tasks at any time, in relation to any changes in the regulations and provisions of service in force.

It is the faculty of the City Hall to proceed with a pre-selection of candidates and candidates for the call to hearings.

The City Hall reserves the right not to proceed with recruitment, in the absence of candidates or candidates eligible for the function.

